
[1]metallurgy

   MET'ALLURGY, n. [Gr. metal, and work.] The art of working metals,
   comprehending the whole process of separating them from other matters
   in the ore, smelting, refining and parting them. Gilding is also a
   branch of metallurgy. But in a more limited and usual sense, metallurgy
   is the operation of separating metals from their ores.

   The French include in metallurgy the art of drawing metals from the
   earth.
